description:
JmapChatClient is not Clone. Every UI crate needs to share the client between a background polling task and UI event handlers. Without Clone, callers must manually wrap in Arc<JmapChatClient>.

Design options (choose one and document):
- Derive Clone if reqwest::Client is Clone (it is — it wraps Arc internally)
- OR wrap reqwest::Client in Arc<reqwest::Client> and derive Clone manually
- After JmapSession is introduced (see session-aware client issue), JmapSession should hold Arc<JmapChatClient> internally so callers can clone sessions cheaply

Document the sharing pattern in lib.rs doc comment with an example showing:
  let session = Arc::new(client.connect().await?);
  let bg_session = Arc::clone(&session);
  tokio::spawn(async move { bg_session.subscribe_events(...) });

Test: assert JmapChatClient: Clone compiles.
